Q-1 What is a worker machine in Kubernetes known as ?
A-1 node or minion

Q-2 A Node in Kubernetes can only be a physical machine and can never be a virtual  machine ?
A-2 False. A Node may be physical or virtual machines.

Q-3 Multiple Nodes together form a ..
A-3 Cluster

Q-4 Which of the following processed runs on Kubernetes Master Nodes ?
A-4 kube-API Server

Q-5 Which of the following is a distributed reliable key-value store used by kubernetes to store all data used to manage the cluster ?
A-5 etcd 

Q-6 Which of the following is responsible for distributing work or containers across multiple nodes ?
A-6 Schedulers

Q-7 Which of the following is the underlying framwork that is responsible for running application in containers like Docker ?
A-7 Containre Runtime

Q-8 Which is the command line utility used to manage a kubernetes cluster ?
A-8 kubectl